      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "In some localities up to 50 cm of snow, and even more in some localities, will fall on Thursday above approximately 1600 m. The new snow will be deposited on a weakly bonded old snowpack. As a consequence of new snow and a sometimes strong southerly wind, avalanche prone wind slabs will form in all aspects. Field observations and weak layers in the old snowpack indicate poor snowpack stability in particular in the regions exposed to substantial precipitation."
